## 🚀 Getting Started

Follow these steps to get the project up and running locally:

### 1️⃣ Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/prakashdb-web/Customer-OnBoarding-System.git
cd Customer-OnBoarding-System

2️⃣ Backend Setup
cd backend
npm install

Start the server (default Express port usually 5000 or as configured):

npm start

3️⃣ Frontend Setup
cd frontend
npm install

Start the Vite dev server:

npm run dev

Open the URL shown in terminal (commonly http://localhost:5173
) to view the app.

📌 Features (Planned / Included)

✔️ Simple dashboard UI for onboarding
✔️ Form pages to capture customer details
✔️ Backend API routes for customer handling
✔️ Modular structure for development scaling

🛠 Usage Tips
Backend API — Use tools like Postman or frontend UI to hit routes exposed through Express
Frontend UI — Hosted locally via Vite with hot‑reload
Environments — Add .env files for backend configuration (like ports, database credentials) but make sure to include them in .gitignore
